{
  "message": "chore(test-utils): scaffold @flywheel/test-utils workspace package\n\nAdds a dedicated place for shared test harness utilities that will be used across:\n- unit tests (package-local)\n- integration tests (apps/gateway)\n- cross-app E2E/contract suites (tests/*)\n\nWhat\u2019s in this commit\n- `packages/test-utils` workspace package with TS config and a single export surface.\n- Placeholder modules for the planned helper domains:\n  - `api` (HTTP request helpers / test server boot)\n  - `agent` (agent lifecycle helpers / fakes)\n  - `db` (ephemeral sqlite setup, migrations, fixtures)\n  - `ws` (subscribe/replay helpers, cursor assertions)\n  - `time` (fake timers / deterministic time)\n  - `assertions` (common matchers and invariant checks)\n  - `logging` (structured test logging + redaction assertions)\n\nIntent\n- Keep tests \u201cstandardized-by-default\u201d so every feature bead can reference a consistent harness.\n- Avoid copy/pasted per-test bootstrapping and keep artifacts/logging behavior consistent.\n\nNotes\n- These are stubs only; concrete helpers should be implemented alongside the first integration/E2E suites.",
